Embattled eThekwini Mayor, Zandile Gumede has spoken for the first since her court appearance in the Durban Commercial Crimes Court over fraud charges. DURBAN - Embattled eThekwini Mayor, Zandile Gumede, has broken her silence. She spoke exclusively to eNCA after meeting with ANC provincial structures. This after she was released on bail following a brief appearance in the Durban Commercial Crimes Court over multi-million rand fraud charges. READ: eThekwini Mayor Zandile Gumede out on bail "I'm so fortunate that I'm one of the leaders of this glorious movement of which everything is done through protocols. Today we had a good meeting with officials and they want to understand what happened," said Gumede. Asked whether she has been sacked? READ: More woes for eThekwini Mayor Zandile Gumede Gumede replied; "No, there's no such thing... as media you must learn to take from the horse’s mouth as you're doing today. For now, I've met with leaders and I went to court  and then that's it". There's been calls for the beleaguered mayor to step aside.